de-puff w/ me :) product details below

I love icing my face first thing in the morning because it felts get the blood flowing and instantly reduces puffiness. Then I do a little face massage with some toner or essence (my fav right now is the @patmcgrathreal one because it’s kind of creamy and feels very nourishing) using my hands. Gua sha unneeded.. your fingers are a great tool and they’re free. 

A hack is to apply a face cream that also serves the same purpose, like the @skinauthority moisturizing lift cream. It instantly brightens, tightens, and lifts (obvi). It is basically like a de-puffing eye cream but for your whole face. Game changer if you feel like a hot air balloon in the morning. 

The @iliabeauty bright started activated eye cream is also a great way to reduce eye puffiness. The ceramic tip at the end doubles as a massage tool and bonus points if you refridgerate before using! So refreshing. 

As always, the @sirenibeauty eye shields are a great and glamourous feeling way to make sure all that product soaks into the area it needs to the most. I leave these on for about 10 minutes. 

Finishing off with a tinted sunscreen from @cerave, this one is so light, gives such a beautiful flush of color, and evens skin tone without feeling makeup-y. I wish it had slightly higher SPF but it makes my skin look so good that I don’t really care. 

Et voila! Enjoy your puff-free day.
